WEBVTT

00:03.210 --> 00:04.250
Previously on "How to Get Away
With Murder"...

00:04.250 --> 00:04.960
-Tell me you didn't.
-Didn't what?

00:04.960 --> 00:06.040
Bang the press secretary.

00:06.040 --> 00:07.710
Isaac overdosed,
Annalise.

00:07.710 --> 00:10.120
So if you think you
need to drink, drink.

00:10.120 --> 00:13.420
Annalise: The Sixth Amendment
was ratified in 1791.

00:13.420 --> 00:17.620
Let's finally guarantee its
rights to all of our citizens.

00:17.620 --> 00:18.750
It's Simon.

00:18.750 --> 00:20.210
He's awake.

00:20.210 --> 00:21.960
Plug this into
your car's data port.

00:21.960 --> 00:23.380
It'll ding me if anyone
messes with the brakes.

00:23.380 --> 00:24.710
Frank: She had Dominick
set up a meeting

00:24.710 --> 00:25.920
between her and the puppy

00:25.920 --> 00:27.460
so she could pay him 100K.

00:27.460 --> 00:29.580
Laurel. Your mom's
been lying to you.

00:29.580 --> 00:31.120
Sandrine: You're having
legal trouble.

00:31.120 --> 00:33.080
Wes: Okay, I'm telling
Laurel about this.

00:34.710 --> 00:37.620
[ Shower running ]

00:37.620 --> 00:39.710
[ Cellphone ringing ]

00:39.710 --> 00:44.620
♪♪

00:44.620 --> 00:46.540
[ Ringing continues ]

00:46.540 --> 00:48.710
[ Handle squeaks, shower stops ]

00:48.710 --> 00:54.710
♪♪

00:58.170 --> 00:59.500
Hello?

00:59.500 --> 01:05.540
♪♪

01:06.710 --> 01:12.710
♪♪

01:13.000 --> 01:15.040
Mrs. Castillo?
Hi.

01:15.040 --> 01:16.960
Hi. Um...

01:18.170 --> 01:20.750
Look, I'm not sure
what this is about.

01:20.750 --> 01:22.960
Sit. I'll explain.

01:22.960 --> 01:25.540
♪♪

01:25.540 --> 01:26.880
Actually,
I just came to say

01:26.880 --> 01:28.790
I'm not okay meeting
behind Laurel's back --

01:28.790 --> 01:30.920
Sit, Christophe.

01:30.920 --> 01:35.040
♪♪

01:35.040 --> 01:41.040
♪♪

01:41.380 --> 01:43.330
Would you like
something to eat?

01:43.330 --> 01:45.920
Uh, perhaps a beer?

01:45.920 --> 01:47.830
I just want to know
what I'm doing here.

01:47.830 --> 01:50.540
♪♪

01:50.540 --> 01:52.960
You're having
legal troubles.

01:54.120 --> 01:55.960
Wallace Mahoney
was killed.

01:58.290 --> 02:00.540
Not sure what that
has to do with me.

02:00.540 --> 02:03.330
But you've had other troubles
with the police, no?

02:03.330 --> 02:06.380
Okay, I'm telling Laurel
about this --

02:06.380 --> 02:08.250
I'll pay you,
Christophe.

02:08.250 --> 02:10.710
Pay me for what?

02:10.710 --> 02:12.670
To stop seeing Laurel.

02:12.670 --> 02:16.960
♪♪

02:16.960 --> 02:22.960
♪♪

02:24.210 --> 02:27.960
Wes: Okay, I'm telling
Laurel about this.

02:27.960 --> 02:29.830
Sandrine:
I'll pay you, Christophe.

02:29.830 --> 02:32.000
Pay me for what?

02:32.000 --> 02:34.290
To stop seeing Laurel.
When was this?

02:34.290 --> 02:35.830
[ Clicks ]
The day before he died.

02:35.830 --> 02:37.210
And Wes never told you?

02:37.210 --> 02:39.460
Do you blame him?
She got in his head.

02:39.460 --> 02:41.170
Why would she want him
to stop seeing you?

02:41.170 --> 02:43.380
Because she's insane,
literally,

02:43.380 --> 02:45.080
or maybe I was wrong.
This was all her.

02:45.080 --> 02:46.080
Don't jump
to conclusions.

02:46.080 --> 02:47.330
You need
to go to Denver

02:47.330 --> 02:49.210
and ask him
exactly what he knows.

02:49.210 --> 02:51.460
She can't go to Denver.
He's been involved in this
since day one.

02:51.460 --> 02:53.460
If he's been working
with your dad or mom,

02:53.460 --> 02:54.290
then it's too dangerous
to go near him.

02:54.290 --> 02:55.460
Fine, then I'll go
to my mother.

02:55.460 --> 02:56.620
We're telling Annalise,
Laurel.

02:56.620 --> 02:57.960
No, she just
got back from DC.

02:57.960 --> 03:00.120
The last thing she needs
is for me to dump this on her.

03:00.120 --> 03:02.040
Do you want
your son back?

03:02.040 --> 03:03.620
Of course.

03:03.620 --> 03:05.330
Then we need Annalise's help.
I'll talk to her.

03:05.330 --> 03:06.880
No, wait!

03:06.880 --> 03:08.380
I should be the one
who tells her.

03:08.380 --> 03:10.750
I know. It's just...
[sighs]

03:10.750 --> 03:13.210
there's something else that
she's dealing with right now.

03:13.210 --> 03:16.380
♪♪

03:16.380 --> 03:17.500
[ Door opens ]
Annalise:
Where's Laurel?

03:17.500 --> 03:19.290
She didn't pick up her phone
when I called.

03:19.290 --> 03:20.790
Well, try again
because I don't want

03:20.790 --> 03:22.290
to have to go
through this twice.

03:22.290 --> 03:23.460
Why? Because
it's about Laurel? I --

03:23.460 --> 03:25.040
I said that we should wait
until she's here.

03:25.040 --> 03:26.880
Connor: I bet it's about
the class action.

03:26.880 --> 03:29.000
The justices were so
impressed they already
decided that you won.

03:29.000 --> 03:31.000
What is it about the word "wait"
that no one understands?

03:31.000 --> 03:32.580
Why aren't you
calling her?
Oliver:
Actually, uh,

03:32.580 --> 03:34.330
while we're waiting,
Connor and I

03:34.330 --> 03:36.290
have some news
we want to share.
Not now, Oli.

03:36.290 --> 03:38.330
-We're getting married!
-We already know that.

03:38.330 --> 03:41.040
Yeah, but we're getting married
with a wedding!

03:41.040 --> 03:43.380
Is it true?
We spent the entire day
in the courtroom

03:43.380 --> 03:44.460
where people fought
tooth and nail

03:44.460 --> 03:46.500
for us to be
gay and equal.

03:46.500 --> 03:48.000
It gave us some feels.

03:48.000 --> 03:50.330
Yeah, but just no --
no "Macarena"

03:50.330 --> 03:52.830
or flash mobs.
Asher: And I say we have
a big, gay bachelor party

03:52.830 --> 03:55.080
with big, gay
stripper packages.

03:55.080 --> 03:58.830
[ Imitates electronic beat ]

03:58.830 --> 04:00.170
Simon's awake.

04:00.170 --> 04:03.460
♪♪

04:03.460 --> 04:05.790
Did he talk?
Can he talk?

04:05.790 --> 04:07.580
I don't know.

04:07.580 --> 04:09.880
Bonnie only said that
he woke up from the coma.

04:09.880 --> 04:11.880
♪♪

04:11.880 --> 04:14.250
Okay, so, there's
still a chance

04:14.250 --> 04:16.000
that the bullet turned
his brain into mush?

04:16.710 --> 04:18.120
[ Knock on door ]

04:18.120 --> 04:19.750
♪♪

04:19.750 --> 04:21.290
[ Door opens ]

04:21.290 --> 04:24.330
♪♪

04:24.330 --> 04:25.290
Hi.

04:28.040 --> 04:29.580
Can we go outside?

04:29.580 --> 04:32.580
♪♪

04:32.580 --> 04:33.880
[ Door closes ]

04:33.880 --> 04:35.670
Did you talk
to Nate?

04:35.670 --> 04:37.830
Yeah, he has an in with
the detective on Simon's case.

04:37.830 --> 04:39.250
He'll call you
when there's an update.

04:39.250 --> 04:41.330
You mean he'll call me
when there's a disaster.

04:41.330 --> 04:42.710
[ Siren wailing
in distance ]

04:42.710 --> 04:44.000
[ Breathes deeply ]

04:44.000 --> 04:46.580
Can't I just feel good
for once?

04:46.580 --> 04:48.170
Just once...

04:51.420 --> 04:52.920
Okay, tell me
what you came to say.

04:52.920 --> 04:54.080
I can take it.

04:58.210 --> 05:00.670
Isaac is still
in the hospital.

05:00.670 --> 05:02.710
A nurse told me
he's on dialysis.
So?

05:04.000 --> 05:05.460
I just thought
you'd want to know.

05:05.460 --> 05:07.000
Like I don't have
enough to worry about?

05:08.620 --> 05:10.250
-Annalise?
-What?

05:10.250 --> 05:12.080
The hospital
just called.

05:12.080 --> 05:13.580
Simon wants
to see me.

05:13.580 --> 05:15.750
♪♪

05:15.750 --> 05:17.960
So much for Nate
warning us about that.

05:19.120 --> 05:20.540
The good news is that
he regained

05:20.540 --> 05:21.830
some of
his ability to speak,

05:21.830 --> 05:24.120
but, obviously,
he's still very weak.

05:24.120 --> 05:25.380
Does he remember
what happened?

05:25.380 --> 05:26.960
All I'm authorized
to tell you is that

05:26.960 --> 05:28.960
his neurological status
has improved.

05:28.960 --> 05:30.170
For example,
it's a good sign

05:30.170 --> 05:31.580
that he asked for you
by name.

05:31.580 --> 05:33.210
Right.

05:33.210 --> 05:34.750
Connor:
What if it's a trap?

05:34.750 --> 05:36.790
Like Simon already
told them that we were
trying to frame him,

05:36.790 --> 05:39.000
and now they're just trying
to catch Oliver in a lie?

05:39.000 --> 05:40.580
Nate would've
told us that.
But what if
seeing Oliver

05:40.580 --> 05:41.830
is what triggers
Simon's memory?

05:41.830 --> 05:43.380
Then at least
we'll know what's coming.

05:44.580 --> 05:46.540
It's gonna be fine.

05:46.540 --> 05:47.580
[ Sighs ]

05:49.920 --> 05:51.500
Mr. Hampton.

05:51.500 --> 05:53.540
Detective Nicholls.
I remember.

05:53.540 --> 05:55.330
So, he was
threatening you?

05:55.330 --> 05:58.170
I don't think
he wanted to hurt anybody.

05:58.170 --> 06:00.580
This is still
an active investigation --

06:00.580 --> 06:03.920
so do not say anything
that could bias Mr. Drake

06:03.920 --> 06:05.750
or distort his memory.

06:05.750 --> 06:07.710
I understand.
Do you?

06:07.710 --> 06:09.500
Because if I sense you
feeding him any information

06:09.500 --> 06:11.330
that could prompt him
to your version

06:11.330 --> 06:13.330
of what happened
that night --
You mean the truth?

06:13.330 --> 06:15.460
I'll arrest you
for obstruction of justice

06:15.460 --> 06:17.420
is my point.
[ Sighs ]

06:17.420 --> 06:19.120
Annalise:
The detectives only know
what you told them.

06:19.120 --> 06:20.710
So just stick
to that story --

06:20.710 --> 06:23.250
that you saw Simon stealing
the files and he shot himself.

06:23.250 --> 06:24.420
I wasn't there
when he shot himself.

06:24.420 --> 06:26.080
Simon's gonna
remember that.

06:26.080 --> 06:28.420
Oliver, look at me.

06:28.420 --> 06:30.670
You're a great liar,
more than you realize.

06:30.670 --> 06:34.170
So just go in there and say
as little as possible.

06:34.170 --> 06:40.120
♪♪

06:40.120 --> 06:41.670
Simon?

06:41.670 --> 06:43.790
♪♪

06:43.790 --> 06:45.120
Hi...

06:45.120 --> 06:51.120
♪♪

06:52.040 --> 06:54.540
Look at you.

06:54.540 --> 06:56.620
[ Door closes ]
You're awake.

06:56.620 --> 07:02.420
♪♪

07:02.420 --> 07:04.670
D-- Did I --

07:04.670 --> 07:06.210
Did I, uh...

07:06.210 --> 07:09.670
♪♪

07:09.670 --> 07:11.540
Did I do it?

07:11.540 --> 07:15.830
♪♪

07:15.830 --> 07:17.710
Did you do what?

07:17.710 --> 07:20.790
Come...

07:20.790 --> 07:23.330
Come out to you?

07:23.330 --> 07:25.080
Oliver: He doesn't remember
anything about the shooting.

07:25.080 --> 07:27.000
Are you sure?
Yes.

07:27.000 --> 07:29.830
For all he knows,
our story's true.
For now.

07:29.830 --> 07:32.460
I looked up brain injuries,
and they say it's like
a computer booting back up.

07:32.460 --> 07:33.920
You might not remember
anything at first,

07:33.920 --> 07:36.620
but eventually,
your memory can come back.
Can come back,

07:36.620 --> 07:38.710
and that hasn't happened yet,
so Oliver's right.

07:38.710 --> 07:40.920
You all need to go home,
breathe

07:40.920 --> 07:42.540
because right now
we're okay.

07:42.540 --> 07:44.170
[ Sighs ]

07:44.170 --> 07:48.290
♪♪

07:48.290 --> 07:49.750
I don't feel good
about this.

07:49.750 --> 07:51.330
Then you shouldn't
have come.

07:51.330 --> 07:52.790
I just think
we should've told Annalise.

07:52.790 --> 07:54.960
That was Bonnie's job,
and she told us we should wait.

07:54.960 --> 07:55.920
Then we at least should've told
Bonnie we were coming --
[ Alert beeps ]

07:55.920 --> 07:57.540
Quiet.

07:57.540 --> 08:03.580
♪♪

08:04.210 --> 08:05.830
Salut, Maman.

08:05.830 --> 08:11.830
♪♪

08:17.540 --> 08:19.750
♪♪

08:19.750 --> 08:21.500
If you want more,
call Dominick.

08:21.500 --> 08:23.540
He'll find me.

08:23.540 --> 08:25.540
Just don't use your name
in case anyone's listening.

08:27.750 --> 08:29.420
I'm not doing this.

08:29.420 --> 08:34.880
♪♪

08:34.880 --> 08:39.210
She's going to break
your heart, Christophe.

08:39.210 --> 08:41.710
She spent her life
trying to fix me.

08:41.710 --> 08:43.960
Now she does the same
with men.

08:43.960 --> 08:48.040
When she realizes she
can't fix them, she moves on.

08:48.040 --> 08:50.330
She did it
with Dominick,

08:50.330 --> 08:52.710
then Frank,

08:52.710 --> 08:53.960
now you...

08:53.960 --> 08:56.210
[ Indistinct conversations ]

08:56.210 --> 08:58.540
Sandrine:
She did it with Dominick,

08:58.540 --> 09:00.880
then Frank,

09:00.880 --> 09:02.750
now you...

09:02.750 --> 09:04.330
Why'd you want him
to stop seeing me?

09:04.330 --> 09:06.330
He was a murder suspect.

09:06.330 --> 09:07.670
I wanted to protect you.

09:07.670 --> 09:10.210
Or you wanted
to protect Antares.

09:10.210 --> 09:11.710
Was the FBI
after Dad again?

09:11.710 --> 09:13.500
Your father didn't know
I saw Christophe.

09:13.500 --> 09:14.920
Wes.

09:14.920 --> 09:16.710
And you admit it then?
You had Dominick kill him?

09:16.710 --> 09:18.080
Of course not.

09:19.170 --> 09:20.380
Then why didn't
you help him?

09:20.380 --> 09:22.750
He left that voicemail
for you.

09:22.750 --> 09:25.540
What voicemail?

09:25.540 --> 09:28.750
Wes left a message on Dominick's
phone the night he died.

09:28.750 --> 09:30.170
I didn't know.

09:30.170 --> 09:32.290
Stop lying.
I'm not lying!

09:32.290 --> 09:34.670
[ Scoffs ]

09:34.670 --> 09:36.120
Regarde-moi.

09:36.120 --> 09:38.330
Regarde-moi,
ma petite.

09:38.330 --> 09:40.250
I was only
trying to protect you.

09:40.250 --> 09:41.880
You're the last person
in the world

09:41.880 --> 09:43.330
who could
ever protect me.

09:45.330 --> 09:48.330
Maybe that's true.

09:48.330 --> 09:50.500
But I would never
hurt anyone you loved.

09:52.880 --> 09:54.500
Please believe me.

09:54.500 --> 10:00.500
♪♪

10:01.750 --> 10:07.790
♪♪

10:08.170 --> 10:10.290
[ Footsteps approaching ]

10:10.290 --> 10:14.540
♪♪

10:14.540 --> 10:16.500
[ Car door closes ]

10:16.500 --> 10:18.210
Hey.

10:18.210 --> 10:20.210
How'd Oliver do?
Not bad.

10:20.210 --> 10:22.040
The detective bought
the whole gay thing.

10:22.040 --> 10:23.750
Well, the gay thing
is true.

10:23.750 --> 10:25.000
Everything else
is not.

10:29.080 --> 10:30.330
I'm sorry.

10:32.080 --> 10:34.000
It's fine.

10:34.000 --> 10:36.710
I should be prepping in case
your father gets a new trial

10:36.710 --> 10:38.420
and not dragging you
into this mess.

10:38.420 --> 10:41.460
After everything
you did,

10:41.460 --> 10:44.120
he'd knock my ass out
if I didn't help you.

10:51.500 --> 10:53.750
Keep your phone close.

11:00.000 --> 11:01.790
[ Car door closes ]

11:01.790 --> 11:03.420
Connor: This isn't
the version of a facial

11:03.420 --> 11:05.380
I was hoping
you were talking about.
You heard AK --

11:05.380 --> 11:07.120
best thing we can do right now
is self-care.

11:07.120 --> 11:08.210
I don't think she meant
have a spa day.

11:08.210 --> 11:09.880
Okay, well,
don't get jelly

11:09.880 --> 11:11.040
if you end up looking like
Oli's daddy

11:11.040 --> 11:12.170
in the wedding photos.

11:14.420 --> 11:16.170
[ Sighs ]
Come with me.

11:16.170 --> 11:17.250
Right now.

11:20.540 --> 11:22.380
[ Whispering ] You better not be
texting your "D" from DC.

11:22.380 --> 11:24.460
I only wrote "Hi."
I'm not gonna send it.

11:24.460 --> 11:26.920
Look, I was okay keeping
my mouth shut when this
was a one-and-done,

11:26.920 --> 11:28.620
but you clearly
have feelings for him.

11:28.620 --> 11:29.960
I don't.

11:31.380 --> 11:33.170
[ Sighs ]

11:33.170 --> 11:35.670
Fine.
The truth is --

11:35.670 --> 11:36.920
I don't know
if I have feelings,

11:36.920 --> 11:38.170
but don't worry.
I'm not gonna act on them.

11:38.170 --> 11:39.460
You already did.
Again.

11:39.460 --> 11:40.710
Because you want
to stay with Asher,

11:40.710 --> 11:42.380
or because Marcus
doesn't live here?

11:43.830 --> 11:45.290
[ Sighs ]

11:49.170 --> 11:50.500
[ Sighs ]

11:52.460 --> 11:55.290
I know it was wrong.

11:55.290 --> 11:56.880
And mean.

11:56.880 --> 11:58.880
But everything's always
so horrible here.

11:58.880 --> 12:01.000
And when I was there,

12:01.000 --> 12:04.960
when we were doing
something good for people,

12:04.960 --> 12:07.920
I guess it was just nice to have
someone only see me as me.

12:10.080 --> 12:11.710
Look...

12:11.710 --> 12:13.460
you did a bad thing,

12:13.460 --> 12:15.750
and you can't take
that part back.

12:15.750 --> 12:17.000
So right now

12:17.000 --> 12:18.580
you need
to make a decision.

12:18.580 --> 12:20.830
Do you want
to be a cheater

12:20.830 --> 12:22.880
or a lying cheater?

12:22.880 --> 12:25.210
Because the truth's
gonna come out.

12:25.210 --> 12:28.750
Just like it probably will
about Simon.

12:28.750 --> 12:31.620
So just...

12:31.620 --> 12:33.670
um, pick the type of person
you want to be.

12:35.540 --> 12:37.080
The rest
is up to Asher.

12:39.580 --> 12:41.500
[ Cellphone ringing ]

12:41.500 --> 12:42.670
Marcus?

12:42.670 --> 12:43.920
No.

12:48.040 --> 12:50.290
This is Michaela Pratt.

12:50.290 --> 12:53.500
Nicholls:
How would you describe your
feelings toward Simon Drake?

12:53.500 --> 12:55.420
Can I be blunt?

12:55.420 --> 12:57.000
I was never a fan,
but we were fine.

12:57.000 --> 12:58.210
Professional.

12:58.210 --> 12:59.620
Well, witnesses say

12:59.620 --> 13:01.500
you were openly hostile
toward one another.

13:01.500 --> 13:03.170
Two hyper-competitive
law students

13:03.170 --> 13:04.460
who had
the occasional squabble --

13:04.460 --> 13:06.330
that's quite
the social anomaly.

13:06.330 --> 13:08.250
Did you happen to have
one of these squabbles

13:08.250 --> 13:10.000
the night of
the Caplan & Gold party?

13:10.000 --> 13:11.620
What are you
so worried about?

13:11.620 --> 13:12.880
You're doing that
fake-ass smile you plaster on

13:12.880 --> 13:14.290
when you're nervous.

13:14.290 --> 13:15.380
Or when I want to cut a bitch
but can't

13:15.380 --> 13:16.670
'cause I'm at
a work function.

13:18.170 --> 13:19.790
Who told you that?
Simon?

13:19.790 --> 13:22.120
Either you shared words
or you didn't, Ms. Pratt.

13:22.880 --> 13:25.210
Okay.

13:25.210 --> 13:26.330
I'm going to ignore
the fact

13:26.330 --> 13:28.040
that you're
trying to manufacture

13:28.040 --> 13:30.210
some kind of haphazard
confession from me,

13:30.210 --> 13:32.420
and instead point out
that you are overstepping

13:32.420 --> 13:34.040
numerous
interrogation guidelines,

13:34.040 --> 13:35.670
which strongly discourage
law enforcement

13:35.670 --> 13:38.380
from correlating innocuous
interactions from the past

13:38.380 --> 13:41.250
to an act
of extreme violence.

13:41.250 --> 13:44.170
So, can we describe
this conversation as "over,"

13:44.170 --> 13:46.710
or do I need to call
my lawyer?

13:46.710 --> 13:48.790
Simon's
remembering more.

13:48.790 --> 13:50.830
Okay, but how do you know
that it was Simon that told
them about the fight?

13:50.830 --> 13:53.000
I mean, that party was packed.
Anybody could've heard.

13:53.000 --> 13:54.420
Or the more likely
scenario --

13:54.420 --> 13:55.920
the computer's
booting back up.

13:57.580 --> 13:59.380
Oliver, you have
to marry Simon.
What?

13:59.380 --> 14:01.080
We give him his dream husband
and a green card

14:01.080 --> 14:02.380
in exchange
for his silence.
I'm not doing that.

14:02.380 --> 14:04.040
Oh, you'd rather us
all go to prison?

14:04.040 --> 14:06.500
Look, I'd rather take the fall
than let you go to jail.
Stop.

14:06.500 --> 14:08.120
The world needs Michaela Pratt
more than it needs

14:08.120 --> 14:09.830
another average white guy
like me.

14:09.830 --> 14:12.080
Or we just have Frank go in
and smother him.

14:12.080 --> 14:13.670
Never say that again!
Enough.

14:13.670 --> 14:15.790
Michaela's right.

14:15.790 --> 14:17.670
I am not letting
Oliver marry Simon.

14:17.670 --> 14:19.040
She's right
in that the only way

14:19.040 --> 14:21.620
to solve this
is to control Simon.

14:21.620 --> 14:23.580
He needs to hire me
as his lawyer.

14:23.580 --> 14:25.290
He hates you.
He doesn't hate Oliver.

14:26.880 --> 14:28.790
I can't go back in there.
You have to.

14:28.790 --> 14:31.580
S-Send Nate in!

14:31.580 --> 14:34.500
Simon doesn't know Nate,
let alone trust him.

14:34.500 --> 14:37.540
And wasn't it your idea to frame
Simon in the first place?

14:37.540 --> 14:40.000
Least you can do now
is to help us turn him.

14:40.000 --> 14:46.000
♪♪

14:50.000 --> 14:56.000
♪♪

14:56.460 --> 14:58.040
You're back.

14:58.040 --> 15:00.210
[ Chuckles softly ]

15:00.210 --> 15:01.750
Of course.

15:01.750 --> 15:06.080
♪♪

15:06.080 --> 15:08.710
What's wrong?

15:08.710 --> 15:11.290
Uh, nothing.

15:11.290 --> 15:13.420
Just...

15:13.420 --> 15:16.420
I've been thinking a lot
about what you said,

15:16.420 --> 15:21.250
and...I'm sorry
that it took almost losing you

15:21.250 --> 15:22.830
to make me realize
how I feel, but...

15:22.830 --> 15:26.080
[ Breathes shakily ]

15:26.080 --> 15:30.540
...I have to be
honest here.

15:30.540 --> 15:33.960
I really like you,
too, Simon.

15:33.960 --> 15:34.960
[ Chuckles ]

15:34.960 --> 15:37.250
[ Chuckles ]

15:37.250 --> 15:39.460
You do?

15:39.460 --> 15:42.380
So much.

15:42.380 --> 15:45.210
Which is why I also
have to be honest

15:45.210 --> 15:47.710
and tell you that...

15:47.710 --> 15:50.040
I really think
you need to hire a lawyer.

15:52.830 --> 15:54.210
Can I help you?

15:54.210 --> 15:55.380
Someone I know has been
a patient here.

15:55.380 --> 15:57.380
I just don't know
if they're still admitted.

15:57.380 --> 15:59.960
Name?
Isaac Roa.

15:59.960 --> 16:02.710
And are you
a family member?
No.

16:02.710 --> 16:04.040
Then I'll need
your name, as well.

16:07.250 --> 16:10.040
Hospital policy.

16:10.040 --> 16:12.250
Annalise Keating.

16:12.250 --> 16:13.540
Let me check.

16:13.540 --> 16:14.790
[ Monitor beeping in distance ]

16:14.790 --> 16:16.750
Annalise.

16:16.750 --> 16:18.960
Did it work?
No.

16:18.960 --> 16:20.290
Then you need
to go back in there

16:20.290 --> 16:21.170
while the detectives
are gone.

16:21.170 --> 16:23.080
He already
has a lawyer.

16:23.080 --> 16:24.880
[ Footsteps ]
Tegan: Annalise.

16:24.880 --> 16:26.210
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A. ]

16:26.210 --> 16:28.170
♪♪

16:28.170 --> 16:29.460
You got this.
Leave.

16:29.460 --> 16:30.960
Okay.

16:30.960 --> 16:34.620
♪♪

16:34.620 --> 16:36.750
You're representing
Mr. Drake?

16:36.750 --> 16:38.380
That would explain
why I'm here.

16:38.380 --> 16:40.210
What I can't figure out
is why you are.

16:40.210 --> 16:43.040
You're okay with a conflict
of interest of this magnitude?

16:43.040 --> 16:44.330
Excuse me?

16:44.330 --> 16:46.620
Simon Drake broke
into your firm's files

16:46.620 --> 16:48.620
in an attempt to destroy
one of your richest clients.

16:48.620 --> 16:50.620
According to Ms. Pratt.
And Mr. Drake?

16:50.620 --> 16:52.210
Has he denied
any of this?

16:53.830 --> 16:56.330
I admire you, Annalise,

16:56.330 --> 16:58.250
ever since I wrote a brief
on your Death Row Appeal

16:58.250 --> 17:00.620
when I was a 2-L
at Stanford.
Your point?

17:00.620 --> 17:02.460
You're not gonna win
this one.

17:02.460 --> 17:04.250
Because your real client
is Jorge Castillo

17:04.250 --> 17:06.380
and not that poor boy
in there.

17:06.380 --> 17:07.920
Anything to make sure
that the files he stole

17:07.920 --> 17:10.040
don't get to the FBI.
We're done.

17:11.420 --> 17:12.750
Does Simon know
who you're working for,

17:12.750 --> 17:14.540
or do we need Oliver
to tell him?

17:14.540 --> 17:18.290
♪♪

17:18.290 --> 17:20.500
I've hired a security guard
to make sure

17:20.500 --> 17:22.960
no unauthorized guests visit
Mr. Drake without my approval.

17:22.960 --> 17:24.750
Oliver is not
on that list.

17:26.080 --> 17:28.040
Go home, girl.
Get some rest.

17:28.040 --> 17:30.120
You look like
you need it.

17:30.120 --> 17:33.120
♪♪

17:39.960 --> 17:42.620
♪♪

17:42.620 --> 17:45.380
[ Paper rustling ]

17:45.380 --> 17:47.380
Sandrine:
I'll pay you, Christophe.

17:47.380 --> 17:48.960
Wes:
Pay me for what?

17:48.960 --> 17:51.960
To stop seeing Laurel.

17:51.960 --> 17:53.620
[ Paper rustling ]

17:53.620 --> 17:58.580
♪♪

17:58.580 --> 18:04.290
♪♪

18:04.290 --> 18:06.330
[ Mouse clicks,
computer beeping ]

18:06.330 --> 18:10.880
♪♪

18:10.880 --> 18:16.880
♪♪

18:18.580 --> 18:19.750
[ Clacks lightly ]

18:19.750 --> 18:25.790
♪♪

18:25.880 --> 18:29.080
Call Dominick.
He'll find me.

18:29.080 --> 18:31.210
Just don't use
your name.

18:31.210 --> 18:32.250
[ Beeps ]

18:32.250 --> 18:34.420
[ Knock on door ]
Laurel: It's me.

18:38.420 --> 18:40.790
You missed study group.

18:40.790 --> 18:42.420
I fell asleep.

18:42.420 --> 18:44.710
Well, luckily,
you have a great girlfriend

18:44.710 --> 18:47.120
who not only brought you
a copy of the outline...

18:47.120 --> 18:49.670
but Buster's.

18:49.670 --> 18:54.080
♪♪

18:54.080 --> 18:57.330
Italian or turkey?

18:57.330 --> 18:58.960
Wes?

18:58.960 --> 19:00.580
What?

19:00.580 --> 19:02.250
You okay?

19:02.250 --> 19:03.540
Yeah.

19:03.540 --> 19:07.750
♪♪

19:07.750 --> 19:09.670
[ Sighs ]

19:09.670 --> 19:12.290
I'm okay to talk more
about it if you want.

19:12.290 --> 19:14.420
[ Papers rustling ]

19:14.420 --> 19:16.120
Talk more about what?

19:18.000 --> 19:19.170
Frank.

19:21.920 --> 19:24.210
Tell me
nothing happened.
Of course
nothing happened!

19:25.750 --> 19:28.170
We talked about it.

19:28.170 --> 19:30.170
So unless there's something else
you need to tell me...

19:32.460 --> 19:33.790
There isn't.

19:35.750 --> 19:37.040
Then we're good.

19:40.000 --> 19:43.000
And I'm sorry if I seem
out of it.

19:43.000 --> 19:45.500
[ Breathes deeply ]

19:45.500 --> 19:46.830
I'm probably just hungry.

19:46.830 --> 19:48.830
[ Chuckles ]
[ Chuckles ]

19:48.830 --> 19:51.580
♪♪

19:51.580 --> 19:57.580
♪♪

19:59.710 --> 20:01.710
We're not gonna study
if we keep that up.

20:05.290 --> 20:07.080
Which one?

20:08.830 --> 20:10.330
Turkey.

20:10.330 --> 20:16.330
♪♪

20:19.580 --> 20:25.580
♪♪

20:28.710 --> 20:30.210
Frank:
You hungry?

20:30.210 --> 20:33.750
Fridge is empty.
I can pick up Buster's.

20:33.750 --> 20:35.580
Why didn't he tell me?

20:37.120 --> 20:39.120
We were together right after
he met with her.

20:39.120 --> 20:41.210
He could have told me.

20:41.210 --> 20:43.210
Now, to be fair,

20:43.210 --> 20:44.790
you never told him
about us.

20:47.290 --> 20:48.710
You can go.

20:48.710 --> 20:50.170
Come on, I'm just
trying to help.

20:50.170 --> 20:51.960
I meant go tell
Annalise everything.

20:51.960 --> 20:53.670
I don't care that she's
freaked out about Simon.

20:53.670 --> 20:54.880
Maybe at least
she can tell me

20:54.880 --> 20:56.380
who I'm supposed
to believe here.

20:56.380 --> 20:58.000
Maybe your mom's
telling the truth.

20:58.000 --> 20:59.380
That's really helpful.

20:59.380 --> 21:01.330
It makes sense.
She never got the message

21:01.330 --> 21:03.080
because Dominick told your dad
about it and not her.

21:03.080 --> 21:05.960
Or she told Dominick
to kill Wes,

21:05.960 --> 21:08.540
and now my child is alone
in some hospital room

21:08.540 --> 21:12.040
because he's been born
into the worst family ever.

21:16.080 --> 21:18.830
You're gonna get him back.

21:18.830 --> 21:20.500
You don't know that.
I do.

21:20.500 --> 21:22.000
You hear me?

21:22.000 --> 21:24.250
No matter
what I have to do,

21:24.250 --> 21:26.210
I'm bringing that kid
home to you.

21:29.750 --> 21:31.380
No more dead people.

21:33.330 --> 21:34.960
I know.

21:40.170 --> 21:42.290
[ Cellphone chimes ]

21:42.290 --> 21:48.290
♪♪

21:50.620 --> 21:56.670
♪♪

21:59.380 --> 22:02.170
Laurel:
You need to go to Denver and
ask him exactly what he knows.

22:02.170 --> 22:03.880
Frank:
She can't go to Denver.

22:05.500 --> 22:08.620
[ Mouse clicking ]

22:08.620 --> 22:10.170
[ Cellphone ringing ]

22:13.790 --> 22:15.170
What now?

22:16.620 --> 22:18.540
I don't understand.
Why would it go off?

22:18.540 --> 22:20.540
It said "mechanical error,"
so it could be anything.

22:20.540 --> 22:22.380
Engine looks fine.

22:29.330 --> 22:31.380
This a new scratch?
Why?

22:31.380 --> 22:33.170
Someone backing into you
would have set it off.

22:33.170 --> 22:35.330
Or someone cut my brakes.
Your brakes are fine.

22:35.330 --> 22:37.210
What about the gas tank?

22:37.210 --> 22:38.790
I checked
the whole car, Bon.

22:40.000 --> 22:42.460
[ Trunk shuts ]
Everything looks fine.

22:42.460 --> 22:44.040
Fine enough
that you'd drive it?

22:46.170 --> 22:47.210
No?

22:48.830 --> 22:50.750
You're gonna be pissed.

22:50.750 --> 22:52.120
Tell me right now.

22:53.960 --> 22:55.830
Laurel and I saw Mommy.

22:55.830 --> 22:57.460
Idiot.

22:57.460 --> 22:59.460
She denies having anything
to do with killing Wes.

22:59.460 --> 23:01.880
Of course she did.
But the minute you left her,

23:01.880 --> 23:04.330
she called Jorge, and now
he's messing with my car.

23:04.330 --> 23:05.500
There's nothing wrong
with your car.

23:05.500 --> 23:06.710
According to you!

23:08.750 --> 23:10.330
[ Sighs ]
Should we flip a coin?

23:12.080 --> 23:13.790
To decide
who tells Annalise.

23:13.790 --> 23:15.000
You're telling her.

23:17.420 --> 23:19.250
[ Sighs ]
[ Car door opens ]

23:19.250 --> 23:25.250
♪♪

23:27.380 --> 23:33.380
♪♪

23:35.790 --> 23:37.750
[ Cellphone ringing ]

23:40.080 --> 23:41.540
Isaac: Annalise?

23:41.540 --> 23:47.540
♪♪

23:56.120 --> 23:57.040
Sandrine:
Once she realizes she
can't fix them, she moves on.

23:57.040 --> 23:59.290
She did it with Frank,

23:59.290 --> 24:00.710
Dominick,

24:00.710 --> 24:02.250
now you.

24:02.250 --> 24:03.670
[ Key clacks,
recording turns off ]

24:03.670 --> 24:08.500
♪♪

24:08.500 --> 24:10.880
Why are you trying
to pick a fight right now?

24:10.880 --> 24:12.670
'Cause I have
a bad feeling.
About...?

24:14.170 --> 24:15.920
That you're only with me
'cause you want to fix me.

24:15.920 --> 24:18.040
That's not true!
It makes sense.

24:18.040 --> 24:19.540
You've spent your whole life
trying to fix your mom.

24:19.540 --> 24:21.120
And now what?
It's my turn?
My mom?

24:21.120 --> 24:25.670
♪♪

24:25.670 --> 24:27.380
[ Knock on door ]

24:27.380 --> 24:29.210
♪♪

24:32.960 --> 24:35.330
Are you alone?
Yes.

24:35.330 --> 24:37.250
Thank God.
What's wrong?

24:39.710 --> 24:41.420
[ Sighs ]

24:41.420 --> 24:43.330
Connor says I have to tell
Asher about Marcus

24:43.330 --> 24:45.000
before we all
go to jail, but...

24:45.000 --> 24:47.380
I don't even know
what I want, so...

24:47.380 --> 24:49.120
can you please tell me
what I want?

24:53.670 --> 24:57.210
I am the last person you want
to be asking about this.

24:57.210 --> 24:59.580
You're the only person
I trust on this topic.

24:59.580 --> 25:01.710
Why? Because I cheated on Wes
with Frank?

25:01.710 --> 25:04.170
No. But...

25:04.170 --> 25:05.500
why didn't you tell Wes?

25:07.080 --> 25:09.170
Was it because you didn't have
actual feelings for Frank?

25:09.170 --> 25:11.290
Like you knew it
was just hormones

25:11.290 --> 25:12.540
and you got caught
in the moment

25:12.540 --> 25:13.790
and you knew
if you told Wes,

25:13.790 --> 25:16.380
it would only make
everything worse?

25:16.380 --> 25:18.170
Worse than the two of us
having a huge fight

25:18.170 --> 25:20.040
on the day he died?

25:25.790 --> 25:28.620
Are we the most horrible people
you've ever met?

25:28.620 --> 25:30.120
No.

25:30.120 --> 25:32.420
We just have
horrible parents.

25:32.420 --> 25:34.620
[ Sighs ]

25:34.620 --> 25:36.170
We're too old
to be blaming our parents

25:36.170 --> 25:37.460
for everything wrong
in our lives.

25:37.460 --> 25:38.960
Neither of us learned
how to be

25:38.960 --> 25:40.830
in a normal relationship
is all I'm saying.

25:40.830 --> 25:43.250
It doesn't excuse cheating,
I know,

25:43.250 --> 25:44.830
but maybe
it does explain why

25:44.830 --> 25:47.830
we'd both sabotage
anything good in our lives.

25:50.540 --> 25:53.210
I would have lost it a long time
ago if I didn't have Asher.

25:54.500 --> 25:56.500
Then tell him that.

25:59.580 --> 26:02.210
♪♪

26:02.210 --> 26:04.420
Maybe Michaela's right.

26:04.420 --> 26:06.460
I should just marry Simon
so he can get his green card

26:06.460 --> 26:09.330
and we're all safe.

26:09.330 --> 26:11.290
Where am I left
in this scenario?

26:11.290 --> 26:13.170
We could be
a throuple.

26:13.170 --> 26:14.540
But, actually,
it's not a bad idea.

26:14.540 --> 26:16.620
Okay, I'm totally down
for a throuple situation,

26:16.620 --> 26:17.790
just not with Simon.

26:17.790 --> 26:19.620
No, no, no. I mean
you two getting married.

26:19.620 --> 26:20.880
I mean,
spousal privilege means

26:20.880 --> 26:23.080
you can't testify
against each other in court.

26:23.080 --> 26:24.790
Maybe we should all
get married -- me and Michaela,

26:24.790 --> 26:26.210
Frank and Laurel...

26:26.210 --> 26:29.210
Bonnie and Annalise.
Yeah,
whatever it takes.

26:29.210 --> 26:30.290
You guys just
have to make sure that, uh,

26:30.290 --> 26:31.920
Michaela doesn't pull
a runaway bride on me.

26:31.920 --> 26:33.330
[ Chuckles ]
Not that she would.

26:33.330 --> 26:37.040
I mean, she loves me, obvie,
but, um,

26:37.040 --> 26:39.210
you know, we're still
working through some...

26:39.210 --> 26:41.170
[sighs]
intimacy issues.

26:41.170 --> 26:42.580
[ Chuckles ] So...

26:42.580 --> 26:46.540
♪♪

26:46.540 --> 26:47.750
What?

26:47.750 --> 26:48.750
Nothing.
Nothing.

26:48.750 --> 26:53.500
♪♪

26:53.500 --> 26:55.420
[ Monitor beeping ]

26:55.420 --> 26:57.500
I read the articles
about your case --

26:57.500 --> 27:00.830
making it sound
like you could win.

27:00.830 --> 27:03.540
Oh, I won't believe it until
I get an actual decision.

27:03.540 --> 27:06.580
But still...

27:06.580 --> 27:08.170
I'm proud of you.

27:10.670 --> 27:12.830
You in pain?

27:12.830 --> 27:14.580
No.

27:14.580 --> 27:16.710
Oh, that's
a good sign, right?

27:19.920 --> 27:22.170
You didn't do this
to me, Annalise.

27:24.420 --> 27:26.580
You know you're not
my doctor anymore,

27:26.580 --> 27:28.960
so you don't need to say things
to make me feel better.

27:28.960 --> 27:30.080
That's not
why I'm saying it.

27:30.080 --> 27:31.250
Do you think
you would've relapsed

27:31.250 --> 27:32.540
if I'd never
walked into your office?

27:32.540 --> 27:33.620
You actually think that?

27:33.620 --> 27:36.710
I wanted to die,
Annalise.

27:36.710 --> 27:38.500
That's why I'm here.

27:38.500 --> 27:41.580
[ Beeping continues ]

27:41.580 --> 27:42.540
I give up.

27:44.580 --> 27:47.040
We're different.

27:47.040 --> 27:48.210
You get things
thrown at you,

27:48.210 --> 27:52.210
you -- you get back up,
and you choose life.

27:52.210 --> 27:54.040
I'm a drunk.
You're sober now.

27:54.040 --> 27:56.670
I almost took a drink
in DC.

27:56.670 --> 27:58.000
Right before
I walked into court,

27:58.000 --> 27:59.830
I panicked, and...

27:59.830 --> 28:01.170
But you didn't.

28:04.670 --> 28:06.460
There you go.

28:06.460 --> 28:07.830
No.

28:07.830 --> 28:11.330
Let me take responsibility
for something for once.

28:11.330 --> 28:14.790
Did you hurt me?
Yeah.

28:14.790 --> 28:17.620
[ Sighs ]

28:17.620 --> 28:19.920
That's on me.

28:19.920 --> 28:22.420
Because I let myself feel things
for you that I shouldn't have.

28:25.170 --> 28:26.880
I felt them, too.

28:28.540 --> 28:30.170
I pushed us there.
No.

28:30.170 --> 28:31.580
I failed you.

28:31.580 --> 28:34.000
[ Inhales sharply ]

28:34.000 --> 28:37.080
I don't need
your apologies.

28:37.080 --> 28:40.170
I just need you
to get better.

28:40.170 --> 28:41.380
Eat, sleep,
get a new kidney --

28:41.380 --> 28:42.710
whatever you need.

28:42.710 --> 28:44.500
Finally get yourself
out of here.

28:44.500 --> 28:50.500
♪♪

28:54.210 --> 28:56.750
This is the last time we can
see each other, Annalise.

28:58.000 --> 28:59.290
[ Breathing sharply ]

28:59.290 --> 29:05.290
♪♪

29:07.710 --> 29:09.380
[ Door opens ]

29:09.380 --> 29:15.380
♪♪

29:15.500 --> 29:16.790
[ Sniffling ]

29:16.790 --> 29:22.500
♪♪

29:22.500 --> 29:28.500
♪♪

29:31.330 --> 29:33.750
[ Cellphone ringing ]

29:33.750 --> 29:36.880
♪♪

29:36.880 --> 29:39.080
[ Sighs ]

29:39.080 --> 29:40.580
Hi.

29:40.580 --> 29:41.710
You with Laurel?

29:41.710 --> 29:44.170
No. What's wrong?

29:44.170 --> 29:46.670
Simon remembered she was
at the party that night.

29:46.670 --> 29:49.500
He's giving his statement
to the detectives tomorrow.

29:49.500 --> 29:51.080
[ Sighs ]

30:02.040 --> 30:03.170
[ Breathes sharply ]

30:06.880 --> 30:08.460
[ Sighs ]

30:14.830 --> 30:15.920
[ Door closes ]

30:15.920 --> 30:18.290
Asher, we need to go home
and talk.

30:18.290 --> 30:19.670
I'll explain why
once we're there.

30:19.670 --> 30:21.880
Explain what?

30:21.880 --> 30:23.210
You love me and you want

30:23.210 --> 30:25.500
to spend the rest
of our lives together?

30:25.500 --> 30:27.420
Or that you're
a horrible human being

30:27.420 --> 30:29.120
who made my worst nightmare
come true

30:29.120 --> 30:30.790
when you boned
Marcus Walker?

30:31.830 --> 30:33.120
You told him?

30:33.120 --> 30:34.460
He put it together
on his own.

30:34.460 --> 30:37.080
Because
I'm not an idiot.

30:37.080 --> 30:38.420
You think
it didn't occur to me

30:38.420 --> 30:41.420
the moment that I saw
you two together?

30:41.420 --> 30:43.080
He's the epitome of everything
you've ever wanted,

30:43.080 --> 30:44.210
but I shoved
the thought away.

30:44.210 --> 30:45.880
I told myself
that I was being small

30:45.880 --> 30:48.830
for even thinking
that you would cheat on me.

30:48.830 --> 30:51.750
Because you loved me.

30:51.750 --> 30:53.750
Those were your words.

30:53.750 --> 30:55.420
[ Voice breaking ] I do love
you -- I just made a mistake.

30:55.420 --> 30:57.880
This wasn't a mistake,
Michaela!

30:57.880 --> 30:59.830
This was you stabbing me
in the heart!

31:02.500 --> 31:04.670
Wes: It's Christophe.

31:04.670 --> 31:06.500
I'm in trouble.
We all could be.

31:06.500 --> 31:08.120
Call me
as soon as you get this.

31:08.120 --> 31:09.830
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

31:14.710 --> 31:17.580
[ Beeps ]

31:17.580 --> 31:19.330
I'm so sorry you have to deal
with all of this.

31:19.330 --> 31:21.000
Simon remembered
that you were at

31:21.000 --> 31:23.290
Caplan & Gold that night.
What?

31:23.290 --> 31:25.580
He's giving a full statement
to the police tomorrow morning,

31:25.580 --> 31:28.080
and they might call you in
for questioning tonight.

31:28.080 --> 31:30.540
What do I tell them?
Nothing.
You're gonna hide.

31:30.540 --> 31:32.580
Frank is on his way to you,
so don't answer the phone

31:32.580 --> 31:35.000
or do anything
until you hear from me.

31:35.000 --> 31:36.290
Okay.

31:36.290 --> 31:38.000
[ Cellphone beeps ]

31:39.460 --> 31:41.250
[ Cellphone clatters lightly ]

31:46.750 --> 31:48.290
Asher:
Did being adored get old?

31:48.290 --> 31:49.420
Or getting alphabetted
on the regular?

31:49.420 --> 31:51.540
Did Gustav not give you
enough massages?!

31:51.540 --> 31:53.420
[ Crying ] Please stop yelling
so I can explain what happened.
[ Door closes ]

31:53.420 --> 31:54.830
You don't care
who you have to step on

31:54.830 --> 31:56.580
or sleep with in order
to claw your way to the top.

31:56.580 --> 31:58.380
We have been through hell,
baby, okay?

31:58.380 --> 32:00.080
It makes us do stupid things
that we know that we shouldn't,

32:00.080 --> 32:02.330
like -- like,
running over DAs

32:02.330 --> 32:04.420
and picking up guns
from crime scenes --
We don't have time
for this.

32:07.380 --> 32:09.420
Simon remembers
Laurel was at the party,

32:09.420 --> 32:12.420
which means he probably
remembers everything else, too.

32:12.420 --> 32:14.170
-Oh, my God.
-Oh, we should have put a pillow

32:14.170 --> 32:15.380
over his head
when we had the chance.

32:15.380 --> 32:17.120
If we tape Michaela's picture
to a pillow,

32:17.120 --> 32:18.290
I'd be happy
to suffocate him.

32:18.290 --> 32:21.580
No one's
suffocating anyone.

32:21.580 --> 32:24.710
But we have to convince Simon
not to give a statement.

32:24.710 --> 32:27.210
And how do we do that?

32:27.210 --> 32:28.920
Oliver
has to go back in.

32:31.170 --> 32:32.580
What?

32:32.580 --> 32:38.580
♪♪

32:40.670 --> 32:41.830
No visitors.

32:41.830 --> 32:43.880
I have some files
for Mr. Drake to sign.

32:43.880 --> 32:45.790
The only people authorized
to enter this room

32:45.790 --> 32:46.960
are medical staff...

32:46.960 --> 32:49.580
And Mr. Drake's lawyer,
Tegan Price.

32:49.580 --> 32:51.170
I'm her assistant.

32:51.170 --> 32:52.380
Even if the guards
fall for that,

32:52.380 --> 32:53.830
Tegan's gonna be
inside the room.

32:53.830 --> 32:55.830
Not if Michaela
does her job.

32:55.830 --> 32:57.750
[ Toilet flushes ]

32:57.750 --> 32:59.420
My God.
Just hear me out.

32:59.420 --> 33:01.000
No.
You're scared
of Jorge Castillo.

33:01.000 --> 33:03.000
I get that, but you are on
the wrong side here.

33:03.000 --> 33:05.250
Actually, that's you.

33:05.250 --> 33:07.170
Move.

33:07.170 --> 33:09.670
You're not a person who gets
bullied into doing anything,

33:09.670 --> 33:11.880
especially by
a corrupt, horrible man

33:11.880 --> 33:13.170
who has nowhere
near the integrity

33:13.170 --> 33:14.750
or intelligence
that you have.

33:14.750 --> 33:18.040
So for me to watch
a woman of your stature

33:18.040 --> 33:20.670
be controlled by a man

33:20.670 --> 33:22.080
is heartbreaking
to me.

33:23.710 --> 33:25.580
I need to tell you
something.

33:25.580 --> 33:27.710
That you don't
have feelings for me?

33:27.710 --> 33:29.210
Yeah,
I got that part.

33:29.210 --> 33:31.920
There is a way for you to get
everything you want here.

33:31.920 --> 33:35.540
I don't remember everything,
but I know Laurel was there.

33:35.540 --> 33:37.670
She was
stealing something,

33:37.670 --> 33:39.040
and now you're all
trying to frame me.

33:39.040 --> 33:43.080
Stop talking
so I can help you.

33:43.080 --> 33:45.170
Hello?

33:45.170 --> 33:47.210
It's Professor Keating.

33:47.210 --> 33:49.250
What you're about
to tell those detectives

33:49.250 --> 33:51.040
is gonna help
put you in jail.

33:51.040 --> 33:52.540
You're all
going to jail.

33:52.540 --> 33:55.330
What this case comes down to
is your word against ours.

33:55.330 --> 33:57.330
And do you really think
a jury's going to believe

33:57.330 --> 33:59.000
the account of
one brain-trauma victim

33:59.000 --> 34:00.790
over four healthy minds?

34:00.790 --> 34:02.620
Especially when there's proof
on your computer

34:02.620 --> 34:04.210
that you were planning
to steal those files?

34:04.210 --> 34:06.250
♪ I'll take it like milk
from a baby ♪

34:06.250 --> 34:07.710
There's no way Simon's
going to confess

34:07.710 --> 34:09.080
to something
he didn't do.

34:09.080 --> 34:10.920
He will if he wants
his green card.

34:10.920 --> 34:12.620
It's called an S-Visa.

34:12.620 --> 34:15.830
And the government grants them
to whistle-blowers.

34:15.830 --> 34:17.960
The only way the Feds give him
whistle-blower status

34:17.960 --> 34:19.460
is if he gives them
the Antares files,

34:19.460 --> 34:21.880
which we don't have because
we lost the hard drive.

34:21.880 --> 34:23.420
Bonnie's taking care
of that.

34:23.420 --> 34:26.620
♪♪

34:26.620 --> 34:28.880
You were working the night
Laurel Castillo's bag

34:28.880 --> 34:30.290
was logged into evidence.
[ Sighs ]

34:30.290 --> 34:31.710
But someone got here
before me

34:31.710 --> 34:33.620
and stole
something out of it.
I don't recall that.

34:33.620 --> 34:35.210
You do, and you're
gonna tell me who it was,

34:35.210 --> 34:36.710
otherwise
you don't get this.

34:36.710 --> 34:38.120
♪♪

34:38.120 --> 34:39.500
♪ I'm stuck
in the belly the the beast ♪

34:39.500 --> 34:41.330
Tegan, wait!
I've listened
to your whiny voice

34:41.330 --> 34:43.080
enough for one lifetime,
Michaela.

34:43.080 --> 34:45.000
My point is you're not acting
like the fearless boss-bitch

34:45.000 --> 34:46.750
you taught me to be.

34:46.750 --> 34:48.880
I warned you, Michaela,
to let this go,

34:48.880 --> 34:50.460
but you were too dumb.

34:50.460 --> 34:52.290
So stop following me,

34:52.290 --> 34:54.540
or I'll get security
to physically throw
your ass on the street.

34:54.540 --> 34:58.790
♪♪

34:58.790 --> 35:01.380
♪ Na ♪

35:01.380 --> 35:03.080
♪ Na, na, na, na,
na, na, na, na ♪

35:03.080 --> 35:04.460
♪ Na, na, na, na, na ♪

35:04.460 --> 35:05.580
♪ Na ♪

35:05.580 --> 35:08.830
You're awake.
Good.

35:08.830 --> 35:10.710
The detective wants
to take your statement tonight

35:10.710 --> 35:11.750
if you're up for it.

35:11.750 --> 35:13.380
Mnh. Cancel it.

35:13.380 --> 35:15.380
You mean reschedule it
for tomorrow.

35:15.380 --> 35:18.250
I mean
cancel it for good.

35:18.250 --> 35:20.290
I got confused.

35:20.290 --> 35:22.420
I didn't see Laurel there
that night.

35:22.420 --> 35:24.040
♪ I'm stuck in the belly
of the beast ♪

35:24.040 --> 35:25.920
♪ The beast, the beast ♪

35:25.920 --> 35:29.040
I get how scary this is,

35:29.040 --> 35:32.120
but Laurel Castillo is
the reason you almost died.

35:32.120 --> 35:35.380
I can't be sure
of that anymore.

35:35.380 --> 35:36.830
Simon, take a moment
to think about it.

35:36.830 --> 35:38.040
I did.

35:40.330 --> 35:42.080
You're fired.

35:42.080 --> 35:44.960
♪♪

35:44.960 --> 35:46.500
[ Cellphone rings, vibrates ]

35:46.500 --> 35:47.790
[ Beeps ]

35:47.790 --> 35:49.170
We're good.

35:49.170 --> 35:51.710
Simon's canceled his appointment
with the detectives.

35:51.710 --> 35:53.670
Laurel's not here,
Annalise.
What?

35:53.670 --> 35:55.120
She was gone
when I got here,

35:55.120 --> 35:56.750
and now she's not answering
her phone.

35:56.750 --> 36:01.380
♪♪

36:01.380 --> 36:04.250
I am open
to turning myself in

36:04.250 --> 36:07.210
for stealing the files
from Caplan & Gold

36:07.210 --> 36:08.710
and for bringing the gun
that Simon Drake

36:08.710 --> 36:10.330
used to shoot himself,

36:10.330 --> 36:12.210
but just know that,
if I do that,

36:12.210 --> 36:14.290
you'll suffer, too.

36:14.290 --> 36:15.580
Why is that?

36:18.000 --> 36:20.580
On this phone is proof

36:20.580 --> 36:22.460
that you called Dominick
many times,

36:22.460 --> 36:24.040
including around
when he went missing.

36:24.040 --> 36:26.210
So if I'm arrested, I'm gonna
give this phone to the police,

36:26.210 --> 36:27.710
and they will find out

36:27.710 --> 36:29.500
that you've been working
for my father.

36:29.500 --> 36:31.250
I don't work
for your father.

36:31.250 --> 36:33.750
He illegally donated
to your campaign.

36:33.750 --> 36:36.290
I have proof of that.

36:36.290 --> 36:38.330
And these are things that
I wouldn't want people to know

36:38.330 --> 36:40.040
if I was running
for Attorney General.

36:41.250 --> 36:42.580
What do you want?

36:45.880 --> 36:47.750
Tell me who killed Wes.

36:58.880 --> 37:00.460
Dieu merci.

37:00.460 --> 37:02.250
Je n'aimais pas l'idée
d'en rester là.

37:04.830 --> 37:06.000
Tais-toi.

37:07.420 --> 37:13.460
♪♪

37:14.170 --> 37:15.880
[ Phone ringing ]

37:19.170 --> 37:20.540
Laurel: It's Laurel.
Leave a message,

37:20.540 --> 37:22.120
but I'll probably
never listen.

37:22.120 --> 37:24.380
[ Cellphone beeps ]
No answer.

37:24.380 --> 37:30.380
♪♪

37:30.380 --> 37:33.250
It killed me
to keep this from you,

37:33.250 --> 37:34.920
but you were going
to the Supreme Court.

37:34.920 --> 37:36.580
You didn't need
more problems.
Stop.

37:38.460 --> 37:40.210
I know you're trying
to protect me.

37:40.210 --> 37:41.830
I can't be mad at you
for that.

37:41.830 --> 37:43.670
Of course you can.

37:43.670 --> 37:46.170
I don't have the energy to be
mad at you anymore, Frank,

37:46.170 --> 37:47.500
or anyone else.

37:49.460 --> 37:52.620
Let's just forgive ourselves
for once,

37:52.620 --> 37:54.540
even if
we don't deserve it.

37:54.540 --> 37:59.500
♪♪

37:59.500 --> 38:01.080
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

38:03.460 --> 38:05.250
[ Phone rings ]

38:05.250 --> 38:07.040
Annalise:
You've reached the voicemail
of Annalise Keating.

38:07.040 --> 38:08.920
Please leave a message.
[ Beeps ]

38:08.920 --> 38:12.290
Annalise, I know
who has the drive.

38:12.290 --> 38:14.920
It's Denver.
He's playing both sides.

38:14.920 --> 38:20.920
♪♪

38:23.920 --> 38:25.670
[ Beeps ]
[ Phone ringing ]

38:25.670 --> 38:29.250
♪♪

38:29.250 --> 38:32.330
She's at it again.

38:32.330 --> 38:34.170
Well, if you don't handle it,
I will.

38:34.170 --> 38:40.210
♪♪

38:40.290 --> 38:44.120
You said you never got Wes'
voicemail from that night.

38:44.120 --> 38:46.040
I told you, Dominick
never gave me the message --

38:46.040 --> 38:48.330
Tell me the truth
for once!

38:48.330 --> 38:50.750
[ Gary Numan's
"Ghost Nation" plays ]

38:50.750 --> 38:53.920
♪♪

38:53.920 --> 38:55.960
You got the message.

38:55.960 --> 38:57.170
I know you did.

38:57.170 --> 38:59.460
I didn't.

38:59.460 --> 39:01.080
I got
your phone records.

39:02.750 --> 39:04.670
These are your mother's
phone records.

39:04.670 --> 39:06.750
You tell anyone where you got
this, and I will deny it.

39:08.790 --> 39:10.250
Same goes for this.

39:14.120 --> 39:16.880
Why did you
call Wes back

39:16.880 --> 39:19.710
10 minutes after he left
Dominick that voicemail?

39:19.710 --> 39:22.880
♪♪

39:22.880 --> 39:26.120
♪ We live in a windswept hell ♪
[ Phone ringing ]

39:26.120 --> 39:28.250
♪ Where dust and death
are neighbors ♪

39:28.250 --> 39:29.670
It's Christophe.

39:29.670 --> 39:33.460
♪ We hide in a perfect storm ♪
I'm in trouble.

39:33.460 --> 39:34.670
♪ Not even God remembers ♪
We all could be.

39:34.670 --> 39:36.460
Call me as soon as
you get this.

39:36.460 --> 39:37.500
♪♪

39:37.500 --> 39:38.830
[ Cellphone beeps ]

39:38.830 --> 39:42.000
I called him back
because I wanted to help him,

39:42.000 --> 39:43.620
to help you both.
No.

39:43.620 --> 39:45.500
You were helping
yourself,

39:45.500 --> 39:48.420
Dad, and your stupid
bank account.

39:48.420 --> 39:50.330
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

39:50.330 --> 39:53.710
♪ We run from the wars of man ♪

39:53.710 --> 39:57.040
♪ From everything you are
and will be ♪
Hello?

39:57.040 --> 39:59.330
♪ We are invisible ♪
What's wrong?

39:59.330 --> 40:00.920
I'm in trouble
with the police.

40:00.920 --> 40:03.420
♪ We are the dead ghost nation ♪
For what?

40:03.420 --> 40:06.500
It doesn't matter.

40:06.500 --> 40:09.420
Just know they might
come after her, too.

40:09.420 --> 40:11.500
And if anything happened to her
because of me...

40:11.500 --> 40:14.880
♪♪

40:14.880 --> 40:17.960
Just do whatever you can
to keep her safe.

40:17.960 --> 40:20.080
Christophe,
let me help you.

40:20.080 --> 40:22.210
I have to go.
Christophe!

40:22.210 --> 40:24.460
♪ When the sky came down ♪
[ Cellphone beeps ]

40:24.460 --> 40:28.250
♪ When the sun went dark ♪

40:28.250 --> 40:30.000
♪ When the night rolls on ♪

40:30.000 --> 40:31.540
If Wes
turned himself in,

40:31.540 --> 40:33.580
it would blow back on me,
Dad, the company.

40:33.580 --> 40:35.170
That was
your biggest fear.
No. No.

40:35.170 --> 40:37.170
'Cause then that would mean
no going public,

40:37.170 --> 40:39.120
no getting whatever money
Dad promised you,

40:39.120 --> 40:40.420
so you --

40:40.420 --> 40:42.580
you killed Wes.
I didn't!

40:42.580 --> 40:44.580
Wes: I have to go.
Christophe!

40:44.580 --> 40:49.830
♪♪

40:49.830 --> 40:52.460
♪♪

40:52.460 --> 40:54.330
[ Sighs ]

40:54.330 --> 40:55.670
[ Cellphone beeps ]

40:55.670 --> 40:56.750
[ Phone ringing ]

40:56.750 --> 41:00.080
[ Vocalizing ]

41:00.080 --> 41:02.380
♪♪

41:02.380 --> 41:03.670
Man: What is it?

41:03.670 --> 41:07.000
He's going to the police.

41:07.000 --> 41:09.380
You need to do something.

41:09.380 --> 41:11.040
Laurel: I always thought
that it was Denver,

41:11.040 --> 41:12.670
that it was Denver
who warned Dad

41:12.670 --> 41:14.500
that Wes was about
to turn himself in.

41:14.500 --> 41:16.000
Or even Dominick!

41:16.000 --> 41:17.500
But it was you!

41:17.500 --> 41:19.000
♪ We are the wind and cries ♪

41:19.000 --> 41:20.670
You and Dad --
You did this together!

41:20.670 --> 41:22.210
[ Crying ]
You killed the one person

41:22.210 --> 41:24.460
that I loved the most
in my life!

41:24.460 --> 41:27.080
Now my son's gonna grow up
without a father!

41:27.080 --> 41:28.750
♪♪

41:28.750 --> 41:31.210
Why? So that you could have
more money?!

41:31.210 --> 41:34.080
Tell me why
I shouldn't kill you right now!

41:34.080 --> 41:35.830
♪♪

41:35.830 --> 41:37.670
[ Sniffles ]

41:37.670 --> 41:42.500
♪♪

41:42.500 --> 41:44.920
Bonnie: Annalise, I know
who has the drive.

41:44.920 --> 41:48.500
It's Denver.
He's playing both sides.

41:48.500 --> 41:50.790
I'm driving to your hotel
right now.

41:50.790 --> 41:51.920
[ Cellphone rings ]

41:51.920 --> 41:52.960
[ Beeps ]

41:52.960 --> 41:55.250
Hi.
It's me.

41:55.250 --> 41:56.580
You alone?

41:56.580 --> 41:57.960
No, I'm with Frank.
What is it?

41:57.960 --> 41:59.420
[ Sirens wailing ]

41:59.420 --> 42:01.540
There's been
a car accident.

42:01.540 --> 42:05.000
♪ When the sky came down ♪

42:05.000 --> 42:08.170
♪ And we heard God laugh ♪

42:08.170 --> 42:11.580
♪ When the righteous came ♪

42:11.580 --> 42:14.830
♪ And they cleansed our sins ♪

42:14.830 --> 42:18.380
♪ Have you ever seen God ♪

42:18.380 --> 42:19.380
♪ With your own eyes? ♪

42:28.210 --> 42:34.210
♪♪

42:36.210 --> 42:42.210
♪♪

42:44.250 --> 42:50.290
♪♪
